paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted BRCA2 variants associated with breast cancer risk in the Kazakh population, focusing on allele frequencies and potential associations with disease.

functional_data.summary: Detected with a higher frequency in breast cancer cases compared to controls.

variants.population_frequency: 15.2% in breast cancer cases, 10.1% in controls
variants.additional_notes: Associated with familial breast cancer in some studies.
key_quotes: In BRCA2, missense mutations of the c.865A>C (N289H) gene were detected with a higher frequency in 15.2% of breast cancer cases compared to controls (10.1%).

functional_data.summary: No significant associations found in meta-analysis.

variants.additional_notes: Contrasting results in studies regarding cancer risk.
key_quotes: Regarding the rs144848 polymorphism in the BRCA2 gene, it has a minor G allele frequency of 24.9% in the Kazakh population.

functional_data.summary: Detected with a higher frequency in breast cancer cases compared to controls.

variants.population_frequency: 30.8% in breast cancer cases, 18.7% in controls
variants.additional_notes: Higher frequency in European vs. Asian breast cancer patients.
key_quotes: In BRCA2, missense mutations of the c.10234A>G (I3412V) gene were detected with a higher frequency in 30.8% of breast cancer cases compared to controls (18.7%).
Minor T allele population frequency of rs4987117 polymorphism of the BRCA2 gene in the investigated sample of 1,800 Kazakhs was 1.1%.
